The '''yellow-throated bush sparrow''' ('''''Gymnoris superciliaris'''''), also known as the '''yellow-throated petronia''',<ref name=avibase/> is a species of bird in the sparrow [[Family (taxonomy)|family]] [[Passeridae]]. It is found in south-central and southern Africa in its natural [[habitat]]s of subtropical or tropical dry [[forest]]s, dry [[savanna]], and subtropical or tropical dry [[shrubland]].

